owl:Ontology.dc:description:
This application level ontology is intended to provide the framework for answering questions like:
1. "How can EarthCube help me?" (Science Engagement), 2. "If I had an EarthCube Workbench, what capabilities could I access through it?" (Workbench) and 3. “What EarthCube software components can I use to get my application working?” (Developers).
It extends the idea of an EarthCube Registry beyond data sets, to a generalized Registry of software components, semantic resources, tools, etc., with descriptive information to facilitate evaluation for reuse.
owl:Ontology.dc:title: Earth Cube Resource Registry Ontology

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A catalogued resource that is in the EarthCube Registry.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ECResource

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A software entity on one side of an interface that executes some kind of processing in response to a request made by an agent on the other side of the interface.
owl:Class.vann:usageNote:
The service presents a set of offerings, each of which entails a resource and one or more operations on that resource.
Each offering also specifies the interchange format for input and output, and the syntax for invoking the operations, including any parameters in the operation signature.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EC Service Instance

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A document that describes the technical characteristics of an artifact or practice, possibly including a description of what it should do, or an explicit set of requirements that it must satisfy.
owl:Class.vann:usageNote:
All resources may have a conformsTo property that should be a link to a specification.
Specifications may be hierarchical, e.g. a profile specification might inherit provisions from a parent specification, and add additional constraints to further restrict usage of the artifact or practice.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EC Specification

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: A document that describes the technical characteristics of an artifact or practice, possibly including a description of what it should do, or an explicit set of requirements that it must satisfy.

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A specification of a scenario for a work item with some specific context and goal.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EC Use Case

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: A specification of a scenario for a work item with some specific context and goal.

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: Software represented in the EC registry
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A packaged set of instructions that can be executed by a machine to perform one or more functions. Distribution might be as source code, an executable file, an installer package, or as a web application that can be invoked via URL.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EC Software

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: A packaged set of instructions that can be executed by a machine to perform one or more functions. Distribution might be as source code, an executable file, an installer package, or as a web application that can be invoked via URL.

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A set of operations, messages used to invoke the operations, and inputs necessary to execute the operations, along with an expected output content and format.
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An Interface/API should have an associated specification document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EC Interface_API

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: A set of operations, messages used to invoke the operations, and inputs necessary to execute the operations, along with an expected output content and format.

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A serialization scheme (data format) for communication between agents.
owl:Class.vann:usageNote:
Most general types are generic formats specified by typical MIME types, but this resource type includes much more granular identification of schemes/Data Types/Data Specification that are specific to particular applications. These generally implement some underlying information model (schema and vocabulary) that enables semantic as well as syntactic interoperability.
An Interchange Format SHOULD have an associated specification that documents its provisions and usage.
Registered interchange formats are intended to provide identifiers for data serialization formats that work with specific applications. Links to registered formats would be via URI values for the inputFormat and outputFormat properties on an Interface/API, Software, or Service resource.
In situations where no specification resource is available to document the format, it is sufficient to simply identify the format as an application specific format. This is the case for various commercial applications that use proprietary formats, as well as for scientific model input and output formats.
The interchange format can be linked to an information model that defines the entities and properties represented using the format.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EC Interchange Format

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: A serialization scheme (data format) for communication between agents.

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An ECResource record for a repository - a place where things may be put for safekeeping.
owl:Class.vann:usageNote: In EarthCube, a repository is often a storage system in which objects may be stored for subsequent access or retrieval.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EC Repository

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: In EarthCube, a repository is often a storage system in which objects may be stored for subsequent access or retrieval.

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A specification of concepts, and optionally relationships representing a conceptualization of some domain of discourse.
owl:Class.vann:usageNote:
Includes a spectrum of resources including controlled vocabulary, thesaurus, information model, taxonomy, glossary, vocabulary....).
For linked data purposes, it is useful to specify the entities and properties of the entities represented by the model using URI references to widely used ontologies.
For discovery purposes in the registry, the entities and properties should be described in English language terms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EC Semantic Resource

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: A specification of concepts, and optionally relationships representing a conceptualization of some domain of discourse.

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An entry in the EC Resource Registry representing a composite software entity that enables execution of a variety of tools e.g. MatLab, ArcGIS.
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The key defining feature is extensibility - with plugin architecture and API-based interaction between components to enable reconfiguration/extension for new problems.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EC Platform

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: A curated collection of descriptions of resources, accessible through one or more interfaces.
owl:Class.vann:usageNote:
Technically a catalog should be a dcat bundled dataset (the metadata collection) and one or more sdo:Services (i.e., the access interfaces).
Implicitly there is also a stewardship/policy component determining management of the catalog.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EC CatalogRegistry

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: A curated collection of descriptions of resources, accessible through one or more interfaces.

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000119: A composite resource that is a collection of other resources assembled into a package for some purpose, and accessible as a single Unit.
owl:Class.resource:example: Docker containers; Bagit, Data on the Web, or ORE packages with heterogeneous content.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: EC Bundled Object

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: A composite resource that is a collection of other resources assembled into a package for some purpose, and accessible as a single Unit.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: a set of requests/permissions to users of a Work, e.g. a copyright license, the public domain, information for distributors
owl:Class.rdfs:label: License

owl:Class.obo:IAO_0000115: An ECResource that is a catalog of other resources. By definition catalogs are datasets.
Resource published or curated by a single agent.
owl:Class.vann:usageNote: The class of all cataloged resources, the super-class of dcat:Dataset, dcat:DataService, dcat:Catalog and any other member of a dcat:Catalog. This class carries properties common to all cataloged resources, including datasets and data services. It is strongly recommended to use a more specific sub-class when available.

dcat:Resource is an extension point that enables the definition of any kind of catalog. Additional sub-classes may be defined in a DCAT profile or other DCAT application for catalogs of other kinds of resources
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Cataloged Resource

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: researcher

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: A researcher is a user who is interested in discovering items in the EarthCube Resource Registry (e.g., tools, data sets, etc.) that they can use in persuing their research.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: In the context of the EarthCube Registry developers are users who wish to find software components that they can integrate into software they are building.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: developer

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: A funder is a type of user interested in understanding what elements of the EarthCube Registry they have funded.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: funder

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: A funder is a type of user interested in understanding what elements of the EarthCube Registry they have funded.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: A repository user is one who is interested in what components in the EarthCube Registry may be relevant to integrate or use in serving their user community.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: repository

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: A repository user is one who is interested in what components in the EarthCube Registry may be relevant to integrate or use in serving their user community.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: unknown

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: It is not known how much, if any, usage there is of this resource.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: A resource with low usage, may be new and so has not yet built up a user community, possibly not widely known (more advertising needed), or it may indicate a resource that has missed its mark.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: Information about the maturity of an entity for which development is planned but is not yet underway (e.g., book contract not yet signed, development project not yet started).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: planning

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: in development >1 year out

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: Maturity information about an entity that is currently being developed but which is not expected to be available for more than another year.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: in development <1 yr out

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: Maturity information about an entity that is in development and is expected to be complete in less than another year.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: Maturity information about an entity that is available but only in draft form or as an alpha release. The entity may not be complete (e.g. specifications, documentation) or thoroughly tested (e.g., software).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: alpha or rough draft

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: Maturity information about an entity that is available but only in draft form or as an alpha release. The entity may not be complete (e.g. specifications, documentation) or thoroughly tested (e.g., software).

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: Maturity information about an entity that is complete and available but has not yet been fully vetted (e.g., may contain bugs if software or has not completed editorial or other review if documentation, etc.).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: beta or complete draft

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: Maturity information about an entity that fully developed, tested, etc. and in production (e.g., a major version or edition has been released).
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: in production

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: Maturity information about an entity that fully developed, tested, etc. and in production (e.g., a major version or edition has been released).

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The individual or organization whose name should appear first in the citation for the resource (for names that come after the first use co-author). While it is possible to have an author and principle investigator be the same individual or organization, author is not the same as nor synonymous with principle investigator. Applicable mainly to documents, reports, memos, etc.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: author

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: The individual or organization whose name should appear first in the citation for the resource (for names that come after the first use co-author). While it is possible to have an author and principle investigator be the same individual or organization, author is not the same as nor synonymous with principle investigator. Applicable mainly to documents, reports, memos, etc.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The individual or organization that has accountability and responsibility for the data and ensures appropriate care and maintenance of the resource.

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: The individual or organization that has accountability and responsibility for the data and ensures appropriate care and maintenance of the resource.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The organization that is responsible for providing the PARR required access to the data.

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: The organization that is responsible for providing the PARR required access to the data.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The name of the individual or organization who is responsible for the data at the point when the data was first created. Applicable for data sets that are an aggregation of two or more data sets or if the data set is the first instance of the signal having been converted into data.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: originator
owl:NamedIndividual.skos:editorialNote: In the EarthCube (EC) context, data includes any and all EarthCube resources irrespective of form (e.g., software, documentation, etc. all count as does traditional numeric data).

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: The name of the individual or organization who is responsible for the data at the point when the data was first created. Applicable for data sets that are an aggregation of two or more data sets or if the data set is the first instance of the signal having been converted into data.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The individual or organization that has ownership of the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: owner

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: The individual or organization that has ownership of the resource.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The individual or organization who is responsible for the initial triage of and answering questions related to the resource.

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: The individual or organization who is responsible for the initial triage of and answering questions related to the resource.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The individual or individuals who are the lead researchers for a grant (i.e. head of the laboratory, research group leader, etc.). While it is possible to have a principal investigator and author be the same individual or organization, principal investigator is not the same nor synonymous with author.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The name of the individual or organization who has processed the data in a manner such that the resource has been modified.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: processor

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: The name of the individual or organization who has processed the data in a manner such that the resource has been modified.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The individual or organization who prepares and issues the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: publisher

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: The individual or organization who prepares and issues the resource.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The individual or organization that supplies or allocates the resource for another entity.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: resourceProvider

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The individual or organization who is providing sponsorship for the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: sponsor

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: The individual or organization who is providing sponsorship for the resource.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The individuals or organizations who are the intended consumers of the resource.

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: The individuals or organizations who are the intended consumers of the resource.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The individual(s) or organization(s) who name(s) should appear after the first name in a citation for the resource (use author to denote the first name in the citation). While it is possible to have a co-author and principal investigator/collaborator be the same individual or organization, co-author is no the same as nor synonymous with principle investigator or collaborator
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: coAuthor

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: The individual(s) or organization(s) who name(s) should appear after the first name in a citation for the resource (use author to denote the first name in the citation). While it is possible to have a co-author and principal investigator/collaborator be the same individual or organization, co-author is no the same as nor synonymous with principle investigator or collaborator

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: Party who assists with the generation of the resource other than the principal investigator
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: collaborator

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: Party who assists with the generation of the resource other than the principal investigator

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The individuals or organizations whose contributions deserve recognition in the citation. owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: The individuals or organizations whose contributions deserve recognition in the citation. Use ISO MD_Identification credit field to identify individual or organizations that should be given acknowledgement only.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The individual who has made a corrective or editorial change to the resource as part of a systematic revision process.

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: The individual who has made a corrective or editorial change to the resource as part of a systematic revision process.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The individual or organization which has provided all or part of the finances associated with the resource.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: A class of entity that mediates access to the resource and for whom the resource is intended or useful.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: The individual or organization who has ownership of the legal right to the resource.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: rightsHolder

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: The individual or organization who has ownership of the legal right to the resource.

owl:NamedIndividual.obo:IAO_0000115: Resource is not available for use, typically because it is still in development.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: not applicable

owl:Axiom.owl:annotatedTarget: Resource is not available for use, typically because it is still in development.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: BFO OWL specification label

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Relates an entity in the ontology to the term that is used to represent it in the the Common Logic Interchange Format (CLIF) specification of BFO2
curator note: Really of interest to developers only

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The concise, meaningful, and human-friendly name for a class or property preferred by the ontology developers. (US-English)
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: editor preferred term

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A phrase describing how a term should be used and/or a citation to a work which uses it. May also include other kinds of examples that facilitate immediate understanding, such as widely know prototypes or instances of a class, or cases where a relation is said to hold.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: example of usage

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An administrative note intended for its editor. It may not be included in the publication version of the ontology, so it should contain nothing necessary for end users to understand the ontology.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Name of editor entering the term in the file. The term editor is a point of contact for information regarding the term. The term editor may be, but is not always, the author of the definition, which may have been worked upon by several people
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: term editor

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An alternative name for a class or property which means the same thing as the preferred name (semantically equivalent) Annotations
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: alternative term

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An administrative note of use for a curator but of no use for a user
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: curator note

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The name of the person, project, or organization that motivated inclusion of an ontology term by requesting its addition.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: ontology term requester

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: For external terms/classes, the ontology from which the term was imported
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: imported from

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An axiom associated with a term expressed using natural language
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has associated axiom(nl)

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: An axiom expressed in first order logic using CLIF syntax
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has associated axiom(fol)

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A URI that is intended to be unique label for an axiom used for tracking change to the ontology. For an axiom expressed in different languages, each expression is given the same URI
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: has axiom label
